value.0:
Hello stranger, my name is Tal'gar Meyne. I am the Czerka Security Manager here in Veles Colony.

I don't think I have seen you around. Are you new here?

Listen, if I don't know you, I doubt anyone here will. I may have a little job for you. But I'll need you to be discreet about it.

What would you say about helping the Czerka Security keep our citizens safe?

Listen, if I don't know you, I doubt anyone here will. I may have a little job for you, but I'll need you to be discreet about it.

What would you say about helping the Czerka Security to keep our citizens safe?

We have reports there is a Mandalorian facility located somewhere in the Wildwoods but we don't know where it is. I sent out a search party a few days ago but they haven't come back yet.

You will have to leave the city, go into the Wildlands and head east. I just want you to recon the Wildwoods, find that facility and come back to me. Got it?
Good. Make sure you come back in one piece!
Have you located the Mandalorian facility yet?
Good work. But you say the facility is locked?
I see. We're going to need to find Captain N'guth and his team.

I sent him and his team off to search for the facility. He hasn't made it back yet. Something might have happened to him. Could you search the Wildwoods and try to find him for me? Mention my name and that you're working for me.
Good. Find him and hurry back!
Have you found Captain N'guth and his team yet?
What happened ?

Outlaws? No, N'guth would never have fallen to those types.

[He takes the dog tags from you and inspects them.] I can't believe he's gone. The only ones who could have gotten the best of him would be those Mandalorians dogs ! [He grabs the key from you.] This must be the key for the facility.

Unfortunately, we don't have a strike team available at the moment. But I assure you we will take care of those Mandalorian scum!

Would you do that? For Czerka, you must avenge Captain N'guth! 

Kill every last one of those Mandalorian raiders! [He hands the key back to you.] 

Take down their leader and the rest will fall too. You better gather a squad for this, It won't be easy.
So, have you taken care of those Mandalorians scum and avenged Captain N'guth?

Good work. A fitting end to a tragic death of our own. [He hands you a supply of credits] 

Take one of these items as a reward, too. For your hard work.
You've done well. Captain N'guth may be gone, but at least we can say he has been avenged.
No, I'm from around these parts.
I'm not interested right now.
Yes, I came on a shuttle from CZ-220.
I'm not interested right now.
I'm listening.
Let me think about it.
Alright. I'll do it.
I'm still looking for it.
Yes, I've located the facility. [Hand Tal'gar a map]
That's right. I couldn't find another way inside.
Let me think about this some more.
Where can I find him?
Let me think about this some more.
No problem, I'll look for Captain N'guth in the Wildwoods.
Not yet.
Yes, unfortunately I found them.
It looked like they were ambushed. Possibly by outlaws. No one was left alive. I managed to find a key and Captain N'guth's dog tags.
I'll be back.
I could go investigate the facility and try to take down the leader.
I'll come back when it's done.
I'm still working on it.
I've taken down the Mandalorian facility. Their leader is dead.
Thank you. [Select reward]
